Rating: 4
First of all, this recipe makes a lot of soup. I actually enjoy spicy food, so I used 1/2 teaspoon of cayenne. I cooked this rather slowly, an hour one day, and then the next day I added the cream and cooked for another hour or so. I wanted to reduce and create a thicker soup. I did not add the crab to the soup as directed, but placed the soup in a bowl and then added about five tablespoons of lump crab to the center of the soup, then sprinkled the soup with green onions. It made for a very nice presentation.

