Rating: 2
Watch out for the celery with this one. The first night we ate it, it tasted overwhelmingly of celery. The next night, the flavors had blended and it was much better. Not a bad recipe, but I'm not sure it was worth the $15 in crab meat. (I used 16 oz, since that's what the container held. Probably a good idea, otherwise I think it would have been overwhelmed by the vegs.) I, too, used my immersion blender to emulsify the veg base before adding the crab meat. I added additional cream, plus a healthy dose of brandy. If I make it again, I'll tweak it and report the results.

